2985	\begin{lemma}[Properness as a morphism property]
2986	  \label{lem:isProper_mathlib}
2987	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.IsProper}
2988	  \mathlibok
2989	  \textit{Provided by Mathlib
2990	  (\texttt{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Morphisms.Proper}).}
2991	  A morphism \(f : X \to S\) of schemes is \emph{proper} iff it is separated,
2992	  universally closed, and locally of finite type. Properness is stable under base
2993	  change: if \(f : X \to S\) is proper and \(g : T \to S\) is any morphism then
2994	  the base change \(X \times_S T \to T\) is proper. Consequently the base-change
2995	  clause that Nitsure invokes (``properness \ldots\ preserved by base-change'')
2996	  applies directly to the proper-support condition below.
2997	\end{lemma}
